<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 8:56PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Anson
and Richmond Counties through 945 PM EDT...
At 855 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles northeast of Wadesboro to 6 miles north
of Cheraw Municipal Airport. Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Hoffman, Ellerbe, Dobbins Heights,
Lilesville, Morven, Norman and McFarlan.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
